<br />Either that, or you can offset your counter so that it ends at zero when counting upward (i.e. start at 256-30), and offset your base address accordingly. I don't remember whether the 6502 has a penalty for crossing a page boundary with an absolute-indexed address, so this may or may not be a good idea.</div>

